---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="Height Conversion: Feet/Inches to Centimeters" description="Easily convert height between feet/inches and centimeters. Includes a reference chart for common heights and the exact conversion formula." keywords="feet to cm, height conversion, inches to centimeters, how tall in cm, feet inches to cm, height chart, convert height">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Length</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Height Conversion: Feet/Inches to Centimeters</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">June 13, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>Whether you are filling out a medical form, shopping for clothes internationally, or just curious how your height compares in metric, converting between feet/inches and centimeters is a skill you will use often.</p>

      <h2>The Conversion Formula</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">1 foot = 30.48 cm | 1 inch = 2.54 cm</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Total cm = (feet × 30.48) + (inches × 2.54)</p>
      </div>

      <h2>How to Convert Step by Step</h2>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong> Convert 5 feet 7 inches to centimeters:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Convert feet to inches: 5 × 12 = 60 inches</li>
        <li>Add remaining inches: 60 + 7 = 67 inches total</li>
        <li>Multiply by 2.54: 67 × 2.54 = <strong>170.18 cm</strong></li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Common Height Conversions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>5'0" = 152.4 cm</li>
        <li>5'2" = 157.5 cm</li>
        <li>5'4" = 162.6 cm</li>
        <li>5'6" = 167.6 cm</li>
        <li>5'8" = 172.7 cm</li>
        <li>5'10" = 177.8 cm</li>
        <li>6'0" = 182.9 cm</li>
        <li>6'2" = 188.0 cm</li>
        <li>6'4" = 193.0 cm</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Going the Other Way: cm to Feet/Inches</h2>
      <p>To convert from centimeters to feet and inches:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Divide the cm value by 2.54 to get total inches</li>
        <li>Divide total inches by 12 to get feet</li>
        <li>The remainder is the leftover inches</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong> 175 cm ÷ 2.54 = 68.9 inches. 68.9 ÷ 12 = 5 feet remainder 8.9 inches. So 175 cm is approximately 5'9".</p>

      <h2>Where Height Units Differ</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>US, UK (informally), Canada (informally):</strong> feet and inches</li>
        <li><strong>Most of the world:</strong> centimeters or meters (1.75 m = 175 cm)</li>
        <li><strong>Medical records:</strong> increasingly metric worldwide</li>
        <li><strong>Passports:</strong> some countries list height in cm, others omit it entirely</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Quick Mental Shortcut</h2>
      <p>Each inch is about 2.5 cm. Each foot is roughly 30 cm. So if someone says they are 180 cm, you can estimate: 180 ÷ 30 = 6 feet (close to the actual 5'11").</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/length" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Length Converter →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/convert/length" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Converter →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
